      <heading>Mon May  1 (Lyia)       :: &amp;rGUILD POLICIES&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>1</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>--&amp;cGuild Purpose&amp;n
The Hunters for the Horn is a guild dedicated to enjoyment
through Roleplay, bringing the greatest amount of
entertainment to the greatest number.
 
However, the guild was not constructed to give you a path
to follow. You will be expected to choose your own Roleplay.
If you ask us &quot;What do I do now?&quot;, we will most likely
answer &quot;Whatever you like.&quot;
 
--&amp;cGuildleader&amp;n
The role of the Hunter Guildleader includes:
     &amp;co &amp;nGeneral guild-direction guidance
     &amp;co &amp;nOut of Character support/advisement, when requested
     &amp;co &amp;nHandling of equipment, guildskills, and sponsorship
       rights
     &amp;co &amp;nGuildquests
     &amp;co &amp;nInduction and promotion of Guildmembers
     &amp;co &amp;nGuild Advertisement/Publicity
     &amp;co &amp;nOut of Character punishment administration
 
The role of the Hunter Guildleader doesn't necessarily include:
     &amp;co &amp;nIn Character leadership
     &amp;co &amp;nSyllabus enforcement
 
If a Guildleader is thought not to be doing his/her job
adequately, first bring it to the GL him/herself in a clear,
concise manner stating what has been infringed, if possible. If
this doesn't work, bring it to the Head GL. Never publically
flame - it is far from constructive.
 
--&amp;cPromotions&amp;n
Hunters of the Horn of Valere are not an organized group of
people or society of some sort at all. They only share a
common goal and &quot;home base&quot;, which usually makes them more
competitive than anything else. Thus, no syllabus or training
guide to &quot;become&quot; a Hunter is to be used.
 
Furthermore, ranks are not to be used as IC indicators of
experience, deed, or importance. If you are a &quot;higher&quot; rank
than another person, you still have no say over that person.
You merely have shown that you deserve a better title.
&quot;Higher&quot; ranks are, however, expected to conduct themselves
in a befitting manner.
 
Please note that ranks are meant to indicate your character's
IC condition. Divisions are not &quot;better&quot; than one another;
they are only different in providing for different kinds of
characters.
 
Promotions will be given based on activity, roleplay, and
merit. If you are consistantly logging on and your roleplay
is improving, you are being a good Hunter. That is expected
of you. You may nominate other guildmembers for consideration
in promotion, but ranks are at the GL's discretion. If you
believe your rank is unfair, take it to the GL like any
other issue.
 
--&amp;cActivity&amp;n
There is no proper way to gauge activity. Someone may set
triggers for idling and no GL, no matter how alert, can
humanly detect whether an online person is legitimately
RPing or not. However, a general idea of how often a
guildmember logs on and RPs is easily calculated.
 
Activity is largely dependant on frequency of RP, but quality
factors in greatly to almost every other issue.
 
If a guild member does not log in without reason for 3 weeks,
he/she will be set to Inactive subrank.
</text>
    </message>
